{
  "texts": [
    "Given a sequence X = {xi}, 15% of the words in the corpus are randomly masked with the [mask] token, creating the new sequence X.",
    "This text is then fed to a multilayered stack of transformer encoders to train a language model parameterized by θ, which reconstructs X by predicting the masked tokens x, conditioned on X:",
    "where C is the index set of the masked tokens in the sequence.",
    "Unlike BERT, which uses a single transformer encoder and is trained through MLM, the feature extractor for the proposed AI-generated review detection model employs ELECTRA-style 47 style pretraining and two transformer encoders.",
    "The generator is trained via the MLM, whereas the discriminator is trained via a token-level binary classification approach."
  ]
}